block content

  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") Apple Health & Medicaid
          h1.display-5.fw-bold Apple Health Rehab Spokane WA: The Medicaid Addiction Treatment Guide
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Learn exactly how to get your medical detox, rehab, and mental health treatment fully covered today.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | April 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 6 min read

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          // TL;DR
          .card.border-0.bg-light.p-4.mb-4
            h5.fw-bold TL;DR / Key Takeaways
            ul.mb-0
              li 
                strong It's Completely Covered:
                |  Apple Health treats addiction as a primary medical illness, funding detox and rehab at 100%.
              li 
                strong Instant Qualification:
                |  If you are a single adult earning less than ~$1,732/month, or have no income, you qualify.
              li 
                strong MAT Included:
                |  Medications like Suboxone and Vivitrol are covered.
              li 
                strong Local Approvals:
                |  Spokane facilities like Frontier Behavioral Health and American Behavioral Health Systems (ABHS) accept Medicaid.

          // Quick Definition & ToC
          h2.mt-2 Quick Definition
          p.lead
             strong Apple Health Rehab in Spokane WA
             |  refers to state-certified inpatient and outpatient addiction centers that accept Washington's Medicaid program, effectively providing zero-cost withdrawal management, therapy, and residential treatment for low-income residents suffering from substance use disorders.

          .mb-5.p-4.bg-light.rounded
            h4.h5 Table of Contents
            ul.list-unstyled.mb-0
              li.mb-2: a(href="#what-is-covered") What Addiction Treatments Does Apple Health Cover?
              li.mb-2: a(href="#eligibility") Am I Eligible for Medicaid?
              li.mb-2: a(href="#how-to-apply") The Step-by-Step Application Process
              li.mb-2: a(href="#local-centers") Spokane Rehab Centers That Accept Medicaid
              li.mb-2: a(href="#mistakes") Common Obstacles and Mistakes
              li.mb-2: a(href="#faq") Frequently Asked Questions
              li.mb-0: a(href="#conclusion") Take Your Next Step

          hr.my-5

          // Intro
          p "Rehab is too expensive." It is the most common reason people in active addiction hesitate to ask for help. While private, luxury rehabs can cost tens of thousands of dollars, Washington State's Medicaid program—known as 
            strong Apple Health
            | —covers comprehensive substance use disorder treatment for low-income residents. If you have no income, you are likely eligible right this second.

          h2#what-is-covered.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-check2-circle.text-primary.me-2
            | What Addiction Treatments Does Apple Health Cover?
          
          p Unlike some states that limit care, Washington aggressively funds recovery. If a licensed clinician assesses you and determines that treatment is medically necessary, Apple Health covers:
          
          ul
            li
              strong Medical Detoxification:
              |  Supervised inpatient withdrawal management to keep you safe when detoxing from fentanyl, alcohol, or benzos.
            li
              strong Intensive Outpatient Programs (IOP):
              |  Group and individual therapy sessions at a local clinic multiple times a week.
            li
              strong Residential Inpatient Rehab:
              |  Living at a dedicated treatment facility for 30, 60, or up to 90 days to rewire your brain and behavior away from your old environment.
            li
              strong Medication-Assisted Treatment (MAT):
              |  Full coverage for life-saving prescriptions like Suboxone (buprenorphine), Vivitrol, or Methadone.

          h2#eligibility.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-person-plus.text-primary.me-2
            | Am I Eligible for Apple Health (Medicaid)?
          
          p In Washington, Medicaid eligibility for adults (aged 19–64) was expanded under the ACA. It is based strictly on your current monthly income.
          
          p As of 2026, a single adult making less than approximately 
            strong $1,732 a month
            |  (before taxes) qualifies. If you have children or dependents, that income limit is significantly higher.

          .alert.alert-warning.mt-3
            i.bi.bi-exclamation-triangle-fill.me-2
            | **Crucially:** If you are currently unemployed because of your addiction and your income has hit zero, you qualify immediately regardless of what you made last year.

          h2#how-to-apply.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-laptop.text-primary.me-2
            | The Step-by-Step Application Process today
          
          p You can apply for Apple Health entirely online. The process usually takes less than 30 minutes, and coverage is often miraculously fast.
          
          h3.h5.mt-4 Step 1: Apply via Healthplanfinder
          p Go to 
            a(href="https://www.wahealthplanfinder.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") wahealthplanfinder.org
            |  and fill out an application. If you meet the income requirements, your coverage often begins on the first day of the month you applied.
          
          h3.h5.mt-4 Step 2: Use a "Navigator" if Overwhelmed
          p If the paperwork is too triggering or you lack internet access, local organizations like 
            strong CHAS Health 
            |  employ "Navigators" whose entire job is to sit down with you and help you fill out the application for free. Walk into any CHAS clinic and ask for a Navigator.

          h2#local-centers.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-building.text-primary.me-2
            | Spokane Rehab Centers That Accept Medicaid
          
          p Once approved, you need to find a "state-certified behavioral health agency" in Spokane that accepts your specific Managed Care Organization (MCO) like Molina, Coordinated Care, or Community Health Plan of WA.
           
          p Almost all major community behavioral health centers in Spokane aggressively accept Apple Health, including:
          ul
            li 
              strong Frontier Behavioral Health
              |  (Outpatient therapy & dual diagnosis)
            li 
              strong Excelsior Wellness
              |  (Youth and young adult focus)
            li 
              strong Spokane Regional Health District
              |  (Methadone and MAT services)
            li 
              strong American Behavioral Health Systems (ABHS)
              |  (Residential inpatient and detox)

          hr.my-5

          // Common Mistakes
          h2#mistakes.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-x-octagon-fill.text-danger.me-2
            | Common Mistakes and Obstacles
          
          ol.mt-4
            li.mb-3
              strong Mistake: Thinking you need an ID to start the process.
              br
              strong Fix:
              |  If you lost your ID on the streets, community centers like CHAS and Compassionate Addiction Treatment (CAT) can help you navigate emergency IDs and Medicaid enrollment simultaneously.
            li.mb-3
              strong Mistake: Choosing the wrong MCO.
              br
              strong Fix:
              |  When you get approved, you choose a plan (Molina, Amerigroup, etc.). Check with your preferred rehab center *first* to ensure they accept the plan you select. You can change plans once a month if needed.

          hr.my-5

          // FAQ
          h2#faq.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-question-circle.text-primary.me-2
            | Frequently Asked Questions
          
          .accordion.mt-4#faqAccordion
            .accordion-item
              h2.accordion-header#faqHeading1
                button.accordion-button(type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faqCollapse1")
                  | Does Apple Health (Medicaid) cover inpatient rehab in Washington?
              #faqCollapse1.accordion-collapse.collapse.show(aria-labelledby="faqHeading1" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion")
                .accordion-body
                  | Yes. Washington State Apple Health covers up to 90 days of residential inpatient treatment if it is deemed medically necessary by an SUD professional.

            .accordion-item
              h2.accordion-header#faqHeading2
                button.accordion-button.collapsed(type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse2")
                  | Do I qualify for Medicaid if I am unemployed because of addiction?
              #faqCollapse2.accordion-collapse.collapse(aria-labelledby="faqHeading2" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion")
                .accordion-body
                  | Yes. Eligibility for adults 19-64 is based strictly on your current monthly income. If you have zero income due to unemployment caused by substance abuse, you qualify for full coverage.

            .accordion-item
              h2.accordion-header#faqHeading3
                button.accordion-button.collapsed(type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse3")
                  | Does Apple Health cover Suboxone or Methadone?
              #faqCollapse3.accordion-collapse.collapse(aria-labelledby="faqHeading3" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion")
                .accordion-body
                  | Yes. Apple Health completely covers Medication-Assisted Treatment (MAT) prescriptions, including Suboxone (Buprenorphine), Methadone, and Vivitrol.

          hr.my-5

          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #0d6efd22 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-hospital.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold Find Medicaid-Friendly Centers
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | You don't have to call twenty different clinics. Head over to our treatment directory where we outline local facilities designed to help folks regardless of income.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/addiction-treatments-support.html")
                i.bi.bi-search.me-2
                | View Treatment Centers

          // About the Author
          .d-flex.align-items-center.mt-5.pt-4.border-top
            .flex-shrink-0
              img.rounded-circle(src="/assets/img/logo.png" alt="Get Sober Spokane Logo" width="64" height="64")
            .flex-grow-1.ms-3
              h5.mb-1 About the Author
              p.small.mb-1 Written by the 
                strong Get Sober Spokane Editorial Team
                |  in collaboration with Washington State healthcare navigators.
              p.small.text-muted.mb-0
                strong Last updated:
                |  April 14, 2026
